A **while loop** repeats code as long as a condition is true.

```javascript
while (condition) {
  // Code runs while condition is true
}
```

While loops are useful when you don't know exactly how many times to repeat.

blocks.code:
let count = 1;

while (count <= 5) {
  console.log('Count:', count);
  count++;  // Don't forget to update!
}

let secret = 7;
let guess = 0;
let tries = 0;

while (guess !== secret) {
  guess = Math.floor(Math.random() * 10) + 1;
  tries++;
  console.log('Guess:', guess);
}

console.log('Correct! Found it in', tries, 'tries');
